<% provide(:title, "Adminstor Ad Inventroy") %>
<p>
<% if !@sport.paypal_email and isAdmin? %>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-11">
			<h3 class="text-warning">You do not have a paypal account email defined for your sports program. You can create your ad inventory but
			 there will be no account to deposit the revenue generated by advertisers until you do so.</h3>
		</div>
	</div>
<% end %>
<p>
<div class="row">
	<div class="col-xs-11">
		<h3 class="text-center">Enter your ad inventory for sale below.</h3>
		<p>
		<h5>If you sell ad space or have corporate sponsors that you deal with directly, create an inventory item to attach that sponsor too. You will not be able to enter the sponsor data and have the sponsor's ad appear on the web site or on our mobile device until you do so.</h5>
		<p>
		<h5>Advertisers will choose from the diferent types of ads and purchaseads based on how often they want their ad to appear. the more they spend, the more oftern their ad will be displayed. You may create as many classes of ad at any price as you like but less is better. The more classes of ads you create the longer the queue cycle will be for them to appear on your mobile and web site.</h5>
		<p>
		<h5>If you choose not to create ad inventory or enter sponsor information, ads will be appear on our mobile device when they visit your site on our mobile app. We encourage to take advantage of using this service to rasie funds for your program.</h5>
		<p>
		<table class="table table-striped table-bordered table-hover">
		    <thead>
		    	<th>Ad Class</th>
		    	<th>Price</th>
		    	<th>General Sale</th>
		    </thead>
		    <tbody>
		    	<% if !@sportadinvs.nil? and !@sportadinvs.empty? %>
			    	<% @sportadinvs.each do |s| %>
				    	<tr>
				    		<td><%= link_to s.adlevelname, sport_sportadinv_path(@sport, s) %></td>
				    		<td><%= link_to s.price, sport_sportadinv_path(@sport, s) %></td>
				    		<td><%= s.active %></td>
				    	</tr>
				    <% end %>
					<%= will_paginate @sports %>
			    <% end %>
		    </tbody>
		</table>
		<% if user_signed_in? and site_owner?(@sport) %>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-3 col-xs-offset-5">
					<%= link_to "Add New Ad Inventory", new_sport_sportadinv_path(@sport), class: "btn btn-md btn-primary" %>
				</div>
			</div>
		<% end %>
	</div>
</div>
